The model utilizes time series data provided by the user to train and make predictions over designated horizons. Each PNC Business Line contributes unique historical data, reflective of its specific operational context, ensuring the model’s inputs are tailored to the precise dynamics of each segment. Development and production datasets maintain consistent characteristics, as they are derived from the same business line, thus preserving representativeness. This consistency supports the model's ability to adapt to and learn from shifts in portfolio behavior, strategic changes, and the introduction of new products, mitigating the risk of representativeness concerns.
